org.projectfloodlight.openflow.annotations

Annotation Type Immutable


  • public @interface Immutable
    This annotation marks a class that is considered externally immutable. I.e., the externally visible state of the class will not change after its construction. Such a class can be freely shared between threads and does not require defensive copying (don't call clone).
    Author:
    Andreas Wundsam <andreas.wundsam@bigswitch.com>
